Vice President Kamala Harris addressed leaders from around the world at the Summit for Democracy, emphasizing the importance of democracy in addressing global challenges. She acknowledged that democracy is currently under threat and called for action to protect and strengthen it. Harris highlighted the need to ensure every eligible American can access the right to vote and urged the swift passage of the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act. She also spoke about the U.S. Strategy on Countering Corruption and the rejoining of the United Nations Human Rights Council. Harris emphasized the connection between human rights and democracy and the importance of gender equity and equality. She concluded with a personal story about a conversation with German Chancellor Angela Merkel, highlighting the significance of democracy in their lives. Harris urged leaders to remember that democracy is the people and called for collective action to deliver for the people.